- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Tezos' focus on safety and its use of formal methods make it likely to fall under this category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): Tezos is a blockchain, which is a distributed system, so this category is also likely. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries): This category is less likely, but Tezos' use as a decentralized smart contract platform could potentially fall under this category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): Tezos' ability to amend its own economic protocol through a voting mechanism could fall under this category. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): Tezos' use of a proof-of-stake consensus algorithm and its focus on formal methods could also potentially fall under this category.
